structure of c programing language :

(1) documentation of programe :

which represent your program's title and discription
which is represent by comments
{discription ya title likh kar bta sakte hai ki mene ye programe me q likha hu}

there are 2 tipes of commnet :
{do tra se hum discription de sakte hai}

    (1) single line comment:wich is represent by //

       e.g.

       // this is a single line comment

    (2) multi line comment : wich is represent by /* ..... */

         e.g.
           /* this is 
                a multi line
                   comment 
           /*
(2) connection of c language libary :
   
    #include <stdio.h> (standard input output header file)
    #include <conio.h> (console input output header file) this is optional

              # : which means predifined
              include : which means to add somthing
              <stdio.h> : using of this we cane access inbuilt function of this file

(3) executation of program :  

void main()
{

}

/* void : here, void is a deta type which does not return value.
    main: main is a function which is represent that this
    is a executatabale function of program
    () : this is represent programe list
    {} : this is represent block of code.
*/
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                           printf():

->in c language printf is a function which is used to display message on output (console screen)
->{c language printf ye function haijo output(result) ke message ko display (dikhata) karta hai}

syntax:

->printf("jo bhi message aapko dikhana ho");

; : semicolon

-> semicolon which is include end of the line
-> it is used to terminate a statement

->{(;)ye semicolon hai ye kisi bhi line ko end karne ke liye jaruri hota hai}

{agar hum c language printf me ek message ke bad dusta messgae likhenge to vo
ek hi line mai aye ga}
  e.g.   ->printf("message1");
         ->printf("message2");
  iska output hoga:
          message1message2
  
{agar humko ye dusri line me likhan hoga to uske liye escape sequence ka use karna hoga}

escape sequence:
(1) \n : ye new line ke liye hai
(2) \t : ye tab space ke liye hai
(3) \\ : ye display slash ke liye hota hai (e.g. isko lgane ke bad output \masshe\ esa aye ga)
(4) \" : ye display double quote ke liye hota hai (e.g> output "message" esa ayega)
(5) \' : ye display single quote ke liye hota hai (e.g> output 'message' esa ayega)
